The paper focuses on developing a learning framework for planning robust grasps for customized grippers in real-time. This involves optimization-based planning, grasp exploration, and collision avoidance, which are all relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework also uses a region-based convolutional neural network (R-CNN) for grasp exploration, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves learning-based approaches, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.ROBOTS).
